        "body": "A fair read of this would be an attempt at 17 U.S.C. § 101 joint work or at least a muddying of the water for what is copyrightable. Since ai-generated anything is not currently settled law. If it cannot be copyrighted no one owns it; if no one owns it anyone or corporation can use it. I am sure buried in a ToS somewhere there is language that states some kind of co-author agreement.\n\nIt is a sad state of affairs we are in no longer being able to trust our tools.",
